Reasoning: We have one sheet, target column is J ("Contract Sent"), existing formulas in J2:J4 are the broken formulas to replace in the same cells. Need implement logic:
- if H contains "N/A" => "N/A"
- else if H is blank => "No"
- else if H is a date OR text "Yes" => "Yes"
Given actual data in H can be datetime or strings. A robust LibreOffice-compatible formula is:
=IF(H2="N/A","N/A",IF(H2="","No",IF(OR(H2="Yes",ISNUMBER(H2)),"Yes","No")))
Dates are stored as numbers in Excel, so ISNUMBER(H2) covers dates. For text "Yes" it returns Yes. Blank returns No. Other unexpected text returns No. Need save, recalc, reload, verify J2:J4 values and sheet names; then output saved path.
